<doc id="518532" wikidata="Q7424964" url="?curid=518532" title="Sasaella">
<text>Sasaella is a genus of Japanese bamboo in the grass family.

;Species
# &quot;Sasaella bitchuensis&quot; – southern Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella caudiceps&quot; – Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella hidaensis&quot; Hishu zasa – Honshu, Shikoku
# &quot;Sasaella kogasensis&quot; Kogashi azuma zasa – Hokkaido, Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella leucorhoda&quot; – Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella masamuneana&quot; Genkei chiku – Japan
# &quot;Sasaella ramosa&quot; Azuma zasa – Japan; naturalized in Great Britain + New Zealand
# &quot;Sasaella sadoensis&quot; – Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella sawadae&quot; – Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella shiobarensis&quot; – Honshu
# &quot;Sasaella yamakitensis&quot; – Honshu

;formerly included
species now included in other genera: &quot;Pleioblastus Sasa&quot;

