<doc id="518539" wikidata="Q2174982" url="?curid=518539" title="Sinobambusa">
<text>Sinobambusa is a genus of East Asian bamboo in the grass family. It is native to China and Vietnam. &quot;Sinobambusa tootsik&quot; also occurs in Japan, having been introduced there during the Tang dynasty (618–907).

;Species
# &quot;Sinobambusa baccanensis&quot; – Vietnam
# &quot;Sinobambusa farinosa&quot; – Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, Jiangxi, Zhejiang
# &quot;Sinobambusa henryi&quot; – Guangdong, Guangxi
# &quot;Sinobambusa humila&quot; – Guangdong
# &quot;Sinobambusa incana&quot; – Guangdong
# &quot;Sinobambusa intermedia&quot; – Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, Sichuan, Yunnan
# &quot;Sinobambusa nephroaurita&quot; – Guangdong, Guangxi, Sichuan
# &quot;Sinobambusa rubroligula&quot; – Guangdong, Guangxi, Hainan
# &quot;Sinobambusa sat&quot; – Vietnam
# &quot;Sinobambusa scabrida&quot; – Guangxi
# &quot;Sinobambusa solearis&quot; – Vietnam
# &quot;Sinobambusa tootsik&quot; – Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, Vietnam; naturalized in Japan including Ryukyu Islands
# &quot;Sinobambusa yixingensis&quot; – Jiangsu

;Formerly included
see &quot;Acidosasa Chimonobambusa Gelidocalamus Indosasa Oligostachyum Phyllostachys Pleioblastus Pseudosasa Yushania&quot; 
