<text>Thamnocalamus is a genus of clumping bamboo in the grass family. These species are found from the Himalayas as well as Madagascar and Southern Africa.

&quot;Thamnocalamus&quot; is closely related to &quot;Fargesia.&quot; The two genera are sometimes regarded as a single genus by some authors.

