<doc id="518659" wikidata="Q6174125" url="?curid=518659" title="Jeff Hyslop">
<text>Jeff Hyslop ( ; born May 30, 1951) is a Canadian actor, singer, dancer, choreographer, and director. Many of his roles have been in musical theatre. His most famous roles were as Jeff the mannequin in the children&#x27;s show &quot;Today&#x27;s Special&quot; and as the title role in the Canadian production of &quot;The Phantom of the Opera&quot; in 1990.

Hyslop was born in Vancouver, British Columbia. He is married to Vancouver-born singer and actress Ruth Nichol. They have one daughter, Gemma Nichol Hyslop, born in 1977 who has a daughter herself, Remmick Hyslop.

==Selected filmography==
